#What is Method Reference in java 8?

Mathod references are a special type of lambda expressions.

They are often used to create simple lambda expressions by referencing existing methods.

Each time when you are using lambda expression to just referring a method, You can replace
your lambda expression with method reference.



we can utilisse the written method which is written already using method reference.



 (::) double colon  (method reference and constructor reference)
